Deliverable 1 — ERD (Entity Relationship Diagram)
What: Design a database schema with 10+ tables covering the full product lifecycle (warehouse → customer door).
Key entities to include:

Vendor, Product, Warehouse, Shelf/Location
InventoryBatch, Order, OrderItem (junction table)
Shipment, Delivery, CourierAssignment
StatusHistory (audit log — this gets you top marks)

How: Draw boxes for each entity, list their columns, and connect them with relationship lines (one-to-many, many-to-many).

Deliverable 2 — Use Case Diagram
What: Map which actors do which actions in the system.
Actors: Vendor, Warehouse Staff, Courier, System Admin
8+ use cases to cover:

Vendor: Upload inventory, track stock, view orders
Warehouse Staff: Receive shipment, reconcile inventory, assign dispatch
Courier: View delivery list, update status, capture proof of delivery, log exception
Admin: Manage users, generate reports


Deliverable 3 — API Documentation
What: Write technical specs for 3 endpoints of the Courier Mobile App.
EndpointPurposeGET /v1/deliveriesGet prioritized delivery list for a driverPATCH /v1/deliveries/{id}/statusUpdate status (e.g., In Transit → Delivered)POST /v1/deliveries/{id}/exceptionsLog an exception (e.g., Customer Not Home)
Each endpoint needs: HTTP method, URL, headers (Auth token), request body, and error codes (400, 401, 404).

Deliverable 4 — Lo-Fi Wireframes (Vendor Dashboard)
What: Sketch 2 screens for Elena (the vendor):

Screen 1 — Inventory Health: Stock levels by category, low-stock alerts highlighted
Screen 2 — Order Lifecycle: Count of orders in each stage (Pending / In Warehouse / Out for Delivery)


Step-by-Step Execution Plan
Given the 2-hour limit, here's how to pace yourself:
TimeTask0–30 minERD — list all entities, define columns, draw relationships30–50 minUse Case Diagram — list actors + use cases, draw the diagram50–80 minAPI Documentation — write all 3 endpoints with full specs80–110 minWireframes — sketch both dashboard screens110–120 minReview — check for 3PL-specific logic, fill any gaps

Key Things to Score High

ERD: Add a StatusHistory or AuditLog table — this alone pushes you to the 9-10 band
API: Always use /v1/ versioning and proper HTTP verbs (GET, PATCH, POST — not everything as POST)
Wireframes: Show insights, not just raw data (e.g., "⚠ 3 items below reorder level" not just a number)
Throughout: Keep the 3PL angle in mind — Elena doesn't own the warehouse, OmniStore does. That distinction should show in your design


