VvisualizeVvisualize show_widgetHere's what earns this wireframe a top score:
Screen 1 — Inventory Health goes beyond just showing numbers. The red alert banner at the top is actionable ("3 items below reorder threshold — action needed before next dispatch window"), not just informational. The stock level bars give Elena a visual sense of urgency without her having to read the numbers. The "Fastest Moving Items" section directly addresses the persona brief — Elena wants to know which items are selling fastest, so she can decide what to restock first.
Screen 2 — Order Lifecycle uses a pipeline view (Pending → In Warehouse → Out for Delivery → Delivered) with live counts, giving Elena a single-glance status of her entire order book. The filter row lets her drill into any stage. The delivery exception warning at the bottom is a 3PL-specific touch — Elena sees directly in her dashboard that 2 packages had issues, with context about the reattempt, without needing to call OmniStore.
UX decisions that score high: consistent nav across both screens, status pills color-coded by stage, the "See all →" links suggest depth without cluttering the view, and the shelf cost metric card reflects the 3PL revenue model (Elena pays per shelf used).

